pokemon.name: Bulbasaur

abilities.description: Powers up Grass-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in harsh sunlight.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Bulbasaur can be seen napping in bright sunlight. There is a seed on its back. By soaking up the sun's rays, the seed grows progressively larger.

pokemon.name: Ivysaur

abilities.description: Powers up Grass-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in harsh sunlight.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: To support its bulb, Ivysaur's legs grow sturdy. If it spends more time lying in the sunlight, the bud will soon bloom into a large flower.

pokemon.name: Venusaur

abilities.description: Powers up Grass-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in harsh sunlight.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Venusaur's flower is said to take on vivid colors if it gets plenty of nutrition and sunlight. The flower's aroma soothes the emotions of people.

pokemon.name: Charmander

abilities.description: Powers up Fire-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low.

hiddenAbilities.description: In harsh sunlight, the Pokémon's Sp. Atk stat is boosted, but its HP decreases every turn.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: The flame that burns at the tip of its tail is an indication of its emotions. The flame wavers when Charmander is happy, and blazes when it is enraged.

pokemon.name: Charmeleon

abilities.description: Powers up Fire-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low.

hiddenAbilities.description: In harsh sunlight, the Pokémon's Sp. Atk stat is boosted, but its HP decreases every turn.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Without pity, its sharp claws destroy foes. If it encounters a strong enemy, it becomes agitated, and the flame on its tail flares with a bluish white color.

pokemon.name: Charizard

abilities.description: Powers up Fire-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low.

hiddenAbilities.description: In harsh sunlight, the Pokémon's Sp. Atk stat is boosted, but its HP decreases every turn.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: A Charizard flies about in search of strong opponents. It breathes intense flames that can melt any material. However, it will never torch a weaker foe.

pokemon.name: Squirtle

abilities.description: Powers up Water-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon gradually regains HP in rain.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its shell is not just for protection. Its rounded shape and the grooves on its surface minimize resistance in water, enabling Squirtle to swim at high speeds.

pokemon.name: Wartortle

abilities.description: Powers up Water-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon gradually regains HP in rain.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its large tail is covered with rich, thick fur that deepens in color with age. The scratches on its shell are evidence of this Pokémon's toughness in battle.

pokemon.name: Blastoise

abilities.description: Powers up Water-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon gradually regains HP in rain.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: The waterspouts that protrude from its shell are highly accurate. Their bullets of water can precisely nail tin cans from a distance of over 160 feet.

pokemon.name: Caterpie

abilities.description: Protective dust shields the Pokémon from the additional effects of moves.

hiddenAbilities.description: Enables a sure getaway from wild Pokémon.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its voracious appetite compels it to devour leaves bigger than itself without hesitation. It releases a terribly strong odor from its antennae.

pokemon.name: Metapod

abilities.description: The Pokémon may cure its own status conditions by shedding its skin.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon may cure its own status conditions by shedding its skin.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its shell is as hard as an iron slab. A Metapod does not move very much because it is preparing its soft innards for evolution inside the shell.

pokemon.name: Butterfree

abilities.description: The Pokémon's compound eyes boost its accuracy.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon can use "not very effective" moves to deal regular damage.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It has a superior ability to search for delicious honey from flowers. It can seek, extract, and carry honey from flowers blooming over six miles away.

pokemon.name: Weedle

abilities.description: Protective dust shields the Pokémon from the additional effects of moves.

hiddenAbilities.description: Enables a sure getaway from wild Pokémon.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: A Weedle has an extremely acute sense of smell. It distinguishes its favorite kinds of leaves from those it dislikes by sniffing with its big red proboscis (nose).

pokemon.name: Kakuna

abilities.description: The Pokémon may cure its own status conditions by shedding its skin.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon may cure its own status conditions by shedding its skin.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It remains virtually immobile while it clings to a tree. However, on the inside, it busily prepares for evolution. This is evident from how hot its shell becomes.

pokemon.name: Beedrill

abilities.description: Powers up Bug-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low.

hiddenAbilities.description: If the Pokémon's attack lands a critical hit, the attack is powered up even further.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: A Beedrill is extremely territorial. For safety reasons, no one should ever approach its nest. If angered, they will attack in a swarm.

pokemon.name: Pidgey

abilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness if it is confused.
The Pokémon's keen eyes prevent its accuracy from being lowered.

hiddenAbilities.description: Prevents the Pokémon from having its Defense stat lowered.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It has an extremely sharp sense of direction. It can unerringly return home to its nest, however far it may be removed from its familiar surroundings.

pokemon.name: Pidgeotto

abilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness if it is confused.
The Pokémon's keen eyes prevent its accuracy from being lowered.

hiddenAbilities.description: Prevents the Pokémon from having its Defense stat lowered.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: This Pokémon flies around, patrolling its large territory. If its living space is violated, it shows no mercy in thoroughly punishing the foe with its sharp claws.

pokemon.name: Pidgeot

abilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness if it is confused.
The Pokémon's keen eyes prevent its accuracy from being lowered.

hiddenAbilities.description: Prevents the Pokémon from having its Defense stat lowered.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: This Pokémon has gorgeous, glossy feathers. Many trainers are so captivated by the beautiful feathers on its head that they choose Pidgeot as their Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Rattata

abilities.description: Enables a sure getaway from wild Pokémon.
It's so gutsy that having a status condition boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat but lowers its accuracy.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: A Rattata is cautious in the extreme. Even while it is asleep, it constantly moves its ears and listens for danger. It will make its nest anywhere.

pokemon.name: Raticate

abilities.description: Enables a sure getaway from wild Pokémon.
It's so gutsy that having a status condition boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat but lowers its accuracy.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: A Raticate's sturdy fangs grow steadily. To keep them ground down, it gnaws on rocks and logs. It may even chew on the walls of houses.

pokemon.name: Spearow

abilities.description: The Pokémon's keen eyes prevent its accuracy from being lowered.

hiddenAbilities.description: If the Pokémon's attack lands a critical hit, the attack is powered up even further.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its loud cry can be heard over half a mile away. If its high, keening cry is heard echoing all around, it is a sign that they are warning each other of danger.

pokemon.name: Fearow

abilities.description: The Pokémon's keen eyes prevent its accuracy from being lowered.

hiddenAbilities.description: If the Pokémon's attack lands a critical hit, the attack is powered up even further.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its long neck and elongated beak are ideal for catching prey in soil or water. It deftly moves this extended and skinny beak to pluck prey.

pokemon.name: Ekans

abilities.description: The Pokémon may cure its own status conditions by shedding its skin.
When the Pokémon enters a battle, it intimidates opposing Pokémon and makes them cower, lowering their Attack stats.

hiddenAbilities.description: Unnerves opposing Pokémon and makes them unable to eat Berries.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: An Ekans curls itself up in a spiral while it rests. This position allows it to quickly respond to an enemy from any direction with a threat from its upraised head.

pokemon.name: Arbok

abilities.description: The Pokémon may cure its own status conditions by shedding its skin.
When the Pokémon enters a battle, it intimidates opposing Pokémon and makes them cower, lowering their Attack stats.

hiddenAbilities.description: Unnerves opposing Pokémon and makes them unable to eat Berries.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: This Pokémon has a terrifically strong constricting power. It can even flatten steel oil drums. Once it wraps its body around its foe, escaping is impossible.

pokemon.name: Pikachu

abilities.description: The Pokémon is charged with static electricity and may paralyze attackers that make direct contact with it.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon draws in all Electric-type moves. Instead of taking damage from them, its Sp. Atk stat is boosted..

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It stores electricity in the electric sacs on its cheeks. When it releases pent-up energy in a burst, the electric power is equal to a lightning bolt.

pokemon.name: Raichu

abilities.description: The Pokémon is charged with static electricity and may paralyze attackers that make direct contact with it.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon draws in all Electric-type moves. Instead of taking damage from them, its Sp. Atk stat is boosted..

pokemon.pokedexEntry: If it stores too much electricity, its behavior turns aggressive. To avoid this, it occasionally discharges excess energy and calms itself down.

pokemon.name: Sandshrew

abilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness in a sandstorm.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in a sandstorm.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: When it curls up in a ball, it can make any attack bounce off harmlessly. Its hide has turned tough and solid as a result of living in the desert.

pokemon.name: Sandslash

abilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness in a sandstorm.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in a sandstorm.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It curls up in a ball to protect itself from enemy attacks. It also curls up to prevent heatstroke during the daytime when temperatures rise sharply.

pokemon.name: Nidoran F

abilities.description: Contact with the Pokémon may poison the attacker.
The Pokémon's competitive spirit makes it deal more damage to Pokémon of the same gender, but less damage to Pokémon of the opposite gender.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat but lowers its accuracy.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its highly toxic barbs are thought to have developed as protection for this small-bodied Pokémon. When enraged, it releases a horrible toxin from its horn.

pokemon.name: Nidorina

abilities.description: Contact with the Pokémon may poison the attacker.
The Pokémon's competitive spirit makes it deal more damage to Pokémon of the same gender, but less damage to Pokémon of the opposite gender.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat but lowers its accuracy.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: When it is with its friends or family, its barbs are tucked away to prevent injury. It appears to become nervous if separated from the others.

pokemon.name: Nidoqueen

abilities.description: Contact with the Pokémon may poison the attacker.
The Pokémon's competitive spirit makes it deal more damage to Pokémon of the same gender, but less damage to Pokémon of the opposite gender.

hiddenAbilities.description: Removes any additional effects from the Pokémon's moves, but increases the moves' power.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It is adept at sending foes flying with harsh tackles using its tough, scaly body. This Pokémon is at its strongest when it is defending its young.

pokemon.name: Nidoran M

abilities.description: Contact with the Pokémon may poison the attacker.
The Pokémon's competitive spirit makes it deal more damage to Pokémon of the same gender, but less damage to Pokémon of the opposite gender.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat but lowers its accuracy.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: The male Nidoran has developed muscles that freely move its ears in any direction. Even the slightest sound does not escape this Pokémon's notice.

pokemon.name: Nidorino

abilities.description: Contact with the Pokémon may poison the attacker.
The Pokémon's competitive spirit makes it deal more damage to Pokémon of the same gender, but less damage to Pokémon of the opposite gender.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat but lowers its accuracy.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its horn is harder than a diamond. If it senses a hostile presence, all the barbs on its back bristle up at once, and it challenges the foe with all its might.

pokemon.name: Nidoking

abilities.description: Contact with the Pokémon may poison the attacker.
The Pokémon's competitive spirit makes it deal more damage to Pokémon of the same gender, but less damage to Pokémon of the opposite gender.

hiddenAbilities.description: Removes any additional effects from the Pokémon's moves, but increases the moves' power.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: A Nidoking's thick tail packs enormously destructive power capable of toppling a metal transmission tower. Once it goes on a rampage, there is no stopping it.

pokemon.name: Clefairy

abilities.description: The Pokémon only takes damage from attacks.
The Pokémon may infatuate attackers that make direct contact with it.

hiddenAbilities.description: Reduces damage dealt to allies.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: On every night of a full moon, they come out to play. When dawn arrives, the tired Clefairy go to sleep nestled up against each other in deep and quiet mountains.

pokemon.name: Clefable

abilities.description: The Pokémon only takes damage from attacks.
The Pokémon may infatuate attackers that make direct contact with it.

hiddenAbilities.description: When attacking, the Pokémon ignores the target's stat changes.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: A Clefable uses its wings to skip lightly as if it were flying. Its bouncy step lets it even walk on water. On quiet, moonlit nights, it strolls on lakes.

pokemon.name: Vulpix

abilities.description: If hit by a Fire-type move, the Pokémon absorbs the flames and uses them to power up its own Fire-type moves.

hiddenAbilities.description: Turns the sunlight harsh when the Pokémon enters a battle.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It can freely control fire, making fiery orbs fly like will-o'-the-wisps. Just before evolution, its six tails grow hot as if on fire.

pokemon.name: Ninetales

abilities.description: If hit by a Fire-type move, the Pokémon absorbs the flames and uses them to power up its own Fire-type moves.

hiddenAbilities.description: Turns the sunlight harsh when the Pokémon enters a battle.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It has long been said that each of the nine tails embody an enchanted power. A long-lived Ninetales will have fur that shines like gold.

pokemon.name: Jigglypuff

abilities.description: The Pokémon may infatuate attackers that make direct contact with it.

hiddenAbilities.description: Reduces damage dealt to allies.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Nothing can avoid falling asleep hearing a Jigglypuff's song. The sound waves of its singing voice match the brain waves of someone in a deep sleep.

pokemon.name: Wigglytuff

abilities.description: The Pokémon may infatuate attackers that make direct contact with it.

hiddenAbilities.description: When it enters a battle, the Pokémon can check an opposing Pokémon's held item.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its fur is the ultimate in luxuriousness. Sleeping alongside a Wigglytuff is simply divine. Its body expands seemingly without end when it inhales.

pokemon.name: Zubat

abilities.description: The Pokémon's intense focus prevents it from flinching or being affected by Intimidate.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon's moves are unaffected by the target's barriers, substitutes, and the like.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: While living in pitch-black caverns, their eyes gradually grew shut and deprived them of vision. They use ultrasonic waves to detect obstacles.

pokemon.name: Golbat

abilities.description: The Pokémon's intense focus prevents it from flinching or being affected by Intimidate.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon's moves are unaffected by the target's barriers, substitutes, and the like.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its fangs easily puncture even thick animal hide. It loves to feast on the blood of people and Pokémon. It flits about in darkness and strikes from behind.

pokemon.name: Oddish

abilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in harsh sunlight.

hiddenAbilities.description: Enables a sure getaway from wild Pokémon.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: This Pokémon grows by absorbing moonlight. During the daytime, it buries itself in the ground, leaving only its leaves exposed to avoid detection by its enemies.

pokemon.name: Gloom

abilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in harsh sunlight.

hiddenAbilities.description: By releasing a stench when attacking, the Pokémon may cause the target to flinch.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: A horribly noxious honey drools from its mouth. One whiff of the honey can result in memory loss. Some fans are said to enjoy this overwhelming stink, however.

pokemon.name: Vileplume

abilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in harsh sunlight.

hiddenAbilities.description: Contact with the Pokémon may inflict poison, sleep, or paralysis on the attacker.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: In seasons when it produces more pollen, the air around a Vileplume turns yellow with the powder as it walks. The pollen is highly toxic and causes paralysis.

pokemon.name: Paras

abilities.description: Contact with the Pokémon may inflict poison, sleep, or paralysis on the attacker.
Restores the Pokémon's HP in rain or when it is hit by Water-type moves. Reduces HP in harsh sunlight, and increases the damage received from Fire-type moves.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon dampens its surroundings, preventing all Pokémon from using explosive moves such as Self-Destruct.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: A Paras has parasitic tochukaso mushrooms growing on its back. They grow by drawing nutrients from the host. They are valued as a medicine for long life.

pokemon.name: Parasect

abilities.description: Contact with the Pokémon may inflict poison, sleep, or paralysis on the attacker.
Restores the Pokémon's HP in rain or when it is hit by Water-type moves. Reduces HP in harsh sunlight, and increases the damage received from Fire-type moves.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon dampens its surroundings, preventing all Pokémon from using explosive moves such as Self-Destruct.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Parasect are known to infest the roots of large trees en masse and drain nutrients. When an infested tree dies, they move onto another tree all at once.

pokemon.name: Venonat

abilities.description: The Pokémon's compound eyes boost its accuracy.
The Pokémon can use "not very effective" moves to deal regular damage.

hiddenAbilities.description: Enables a sure getaway from wild Pokémon.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its coat of thin, stiff hair that covers its entire body is said to have evolved for protection. Its large eyes never fail to spot even miniscule prey.

pokemon.name: Venomoth

abilities.description: Protective dust shields the Pokémon from the additional effects of moves.
The Pokémon can use "not very effective" moves to deal regular damage.

hiddenAbilities.description: Makes status moves more likely to miss the Pokémon.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Venomoth are nocturnal--they only are active at night. Their favorite prey are insects that gather around streetlights, attracted by the light in the darkness.

pokemon.name: Diglett

abilities.description: Prevents opposing Pokémon from fleeing from battle.
Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness in a sandstorm.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the power of Rock-, Ground-, and Steel-type moves in a sandstorm.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Diglett are raised in most farms. The reason is simple--wherever they burrow, the soil is left perfectly tilled for growing delicious crops.

pokemon.name: Dugtrio

abilities.description: Prevents opposing Pokémon from fleeing from battle.
Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness in a sandstorm.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the power of Rock-, Ground-, and Steel-type moves in a sandstorm.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Because the triplets originally split from one body, they think exactly alike. They work cooperatively to burrow endlessly through the ground.

pokemon.name: Meowth

abilities.description: The Pokémon may pick up an item another Pokémon used during a battle. It may pick up items outside of battle, too.
Powers up weak moves so the Pokémon can deal more damage with them.

hiddenAbilities.description: Unnerves opposing Pokémon and makes them unable to eat Berries.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Meowth withdraw their sharp claws into their paws to silently sneak about. For some reason, this Pokémon loves shiny coins that glitter with light.

pokemon.name: Persian

abilities.description: The Pokémon's limber body prevents it from being paralyzed.
Powers up weak moves so the Pokémon can deal more damage with them.

hiddenAbilities.description: Unnerves opposing Pokémon and makes them unable to eat Berries.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: A Persian's six bold whiskers sense air movements to determine what is in its vicinity. It becomes docile if grabbed by the whiskers.

pokemon.name: Psyduck

abilities.description: The Pokémon dampens its surroundings, preventing all Pokémon from using explosive moves such as Self-Destruct.
Eliminates the effects of weather.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in rain.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: When its headache intensifies, it starts using strange powers. However, it has no recollection of its powers, so it always looks befuddled and bewildered.

pokemon.name: Golduck

abilities.description: The Pokémon dampens its surroundings, preventing all Pokémon from using explosive moves such as Self-Destruct.
Eliminates the effects of weather.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in rain.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: A Golduck is an adept swimmer. It sometimes joins competitive swimmers in training. It uses psychic powers when its forehead shimmers with light.

pokemon.name: Mankey

abilities.description: The Pokémon is full of vitality, and that prevents it from falling asleep.
The Pokémon is angered when it takes a critical hit, and that maxes its Attack stat.

hiddenAbilities.description: If the Pokémon has any stat lowered by an opposing Pokémon, its Attack stat will be boosted sharply.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: When it starts shaking and its nasal breathing turns rough, it's a sure sign of anger. However, since this happens instantly, there is no time to flee.

pokemon.name: Primeape

abilities.description: The Pokémon is full of vitality, and that prevents it from falling asleep.
The Pokémon is angered when it takes a critical hit, and that maxes its Attack stat.

hiddenAbilities.description: If the Pokémon has any stat lowered by an opposing Pokémon, its Attack stat will be boosted sharply.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: When it becomes furious, its blood circulation becomes more robust, and its muscles are made stronger. But it also becomes much less intelligent.

pokemon.name: Growlithe

abilities.description: If hit by a Fire-type move, the Pokémon absorbs the flames and uses them to power up its own Fire-type moves.
When the Pokémon enters a battle, it intimidates opposing Pokémon and makes them cower, lowering their Attack stats.

hiddenAbilities.description: When the Pokémon is hit by a Dark-type attack, its Attack stat is boosted by its sense of justice.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its superb sense of smell ensures that this Pokémon won't forget any scent, no matter what. It uses its sense of smell to detect the emotions of others.

pokemon.name: Arcanine

abilities.description: If hit by a Fire-type move, the Pokémon absorbs the flames and uses them to power up its own Fire-type moves.
When the Pokémon enters a battle, it intimidates opposing Pokémon and makes them cower, lowering their Attack stats.

hiddenAbilities.description: When the Pokémon is hit by a Dark-type attack, its Attack stat is boosted by its sense of justice.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: This fleet-footed Pokémon is said to run over 6,200 miles in a single day and night. The fire that blazes wildly within its body is its source of power.

pokemon.name: Poliwag

abilities.description: If hit by a Water-type move, the Pokémon has its HP restored instead of taking damage.
The Pokémon dampens its surroundings, preventing all Pokémon from using explosive moves such as Self-Destruct.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in rain.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It is possible to see this Pokémon's spiral innards right through its thin skin. However, the skin is also very flexible. Even sharp fangs bounce right off it.

pokemon.name: Poliwhirl

abilities.description: If hit by a Water-type move, the Pokémon has its HP restored instead of taking damage.
The Pokémon dampens its surroundings, preventing all Pokémon from using explosive moves such as Self-Destruct.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in rain.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its body surface is always wet and slick with an oily fluid. Because of this greasy covering, it can easily slip and slide out of the clutches of any enemy in battle.

pokemon.name: Poliwrath

abilities.description: If hit by a Water-type move, the Pokémon has its HP restored instead of taking damage.
The Pokémon dampens its surroundings, preventing all Pokémon from using explosive moves such as Self-Destruct.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in rain.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its highly developed muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. This Pokémon can swim back and forth across the Pacific Ocean without effort.

pokemon.name: Abra

abilities.description: If the Pokémon is burned, paralyzed, or poisoned by another Pokémon, that Pokémon will be inflicted with the same status condition.
The Pokémon's intense focus prevents it from flinching or being affected by Intimidate.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon only takes damage from attacks.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: A Pokémon that sleeps 18 hours a day. Observation revealed that it uses Teleport to change its location once every hour.

pokemon.name: Kadabra

abilities.description: If the Pokémon is burned, paralyzed, or poisoned by another Pokémon, that Pokémon will be inflicted with the same status condition.
The Pokémon's intense focus prevents it from flinching or being affected by Intimidate.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon only takes damage from attacks.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It is rumored that a boy with psychic abilities suddenly transformed into Kadabra while he was assisting research into extrasensory powers.

pokemon.name: Alakazam

abilities.description: If the Pokémon is burned, paralyzed, or poisoned by another Pokémon, that Pokémon will be inflicted with the same status condition.
The Pokémon's intense focus prevents it from flinching or being affected by Intimidate.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon only takes damage from attacks.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: While it has strong psychic abilities and high intelligence, an Alakazam's muscles are very weak. It uses psychic power to move its body.

pokemon.name: Machop

abilities.description: The Pokémon employs no-guard tactics to ensure incoming and outgoing attacks always land.
It's so gutsy that having a status condition boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon's determination boosts its Speed stat every time it flinches.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It continually undertakes strenuous training to master all forms of martial arts. Its strength lets it easily hoist a sumo wrestler onto its shoulders.

pokemon.name: Machoke

abilities.description: The Pokémon employs no-guard tactics to ensure incoming and outgoing attacks always land.
It's so gutsy that having a status condition boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon's determination boosts its Speed stat every time it flinches.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: A belt is worn by a Machoke to keep its overwhelming power under control. Because it is so dangerous, no one has ever removed the belt.

pokemon.name: Machamp

abilities.description: The Pokémon employs no-guard tactics to ensure incoming and outgoing attacks always land.
It's so gutsy that having a status condition boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon's determination boosts its Speed stat every time it flinches.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It is impossible to defend against punches and chops doled out by its four arms. Its fighting spirit flares up when it faces a tough opponent.

pokemon.name: Bellsprout

abilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in harsh sunlight.

hiddenAbilities.description: If the Pokémon is holding a Berry to be eaten when its HP is low, it will instead eat the Berry when its HP drops to half or less.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: A Bellsprout's thin and flexible body lets it bend and sway to avoid any attack, however strong it may be. From its mouth, it leaks a fluid that melts even iron.

pokemon.name: Weepinbell

abilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in harsh sunlight.

hiddenAbilities.description: If the Pokémon is holding a Berry to be eaten when its HP is low, it will instead eat the Berry when its HP drops to half or less.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: At night, a Weepinbell hangs on to a tree branch with its hooked rear and sleeps. If it moves around in its sleep, it may wake up to find itself on the ground.

pokemon.name: Victreebel

abilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in harsh sunlight.

hiddenAbilities.description: If the Pokémon is holding a Berry to be eaten when its HP is low, it will instead eat the Berry when its HP drops to half or less.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: The long vine extending from its head is waved about as if it were a living thing to attract prey. When an unsuspecting victim approaches, it is swallowed whole.

pokemon.name: Tentacool

abilities.description: Prevents other Pokémon's moves or Abilities from lowering the Pokémon's stats.
The strong stench of the Pokémon's oozed liquid damages attackers that use HP-draining moves.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon gradually regains HP in rain.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its body is almost entirely composed of water. It ensnares its foe with its two long tentacles, then stabs with the poison stingers at their tips.

pokemon.name: Tentacruel

abilities.description: Prevents other Pokémon's moves or Abilities from lowering the Pokémon's stats.
The strong stench of the Pokémon's oozed liquid damages attackers that use HP-draining moves.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon gradually regains HP in rain.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It lives in complex rock formations on the ocean floor and traps prey using its 80 tentacles. Its red orbs glow when it grows excited or agitated.

pokemon.name: Geodude

abilities.description: The Pokémon cannot be knocked out by a single hit as long as its HP is full. One-hit KO moves will also fail to knock it out.

pokemon.name: Magmar

pokemon.name: Tauros

pokemon.name: Magikarp

pokemon.name: Gyarados

pokemon.name: Lapras

hiddenAbilities.description: Cures the Pokémon's status conditions in rain.

pokemon.name: Ditto

pokemon.name: Eevee

pokemon.name: Vaporeon

pokemon.name: Jolteon

pokemon.name: Kabutops

pokemon.pokedexEntry: A Pokémon that was created by genetic manipulation. However, even though the scientific power of humans made its body, they failed to give it a warm heart.

pokemon.name: Bayleef

pokemon.name: Meganium

hiddenAbilities.description: Prevents status conditions in harsh sunlight.

pokemon.name: Quilava

pokemon.name: Typhlosion

pokemon.name: Croconaw

pokemon.name: Feraligatr

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It opens its huge mouth to intimidate enemies. In battle, it runs using its thick and powerful hind legs to charge the foe with incredible speed.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon reflects status moves instead of getting hit by them.

pokemon.name: Bellossom

hiddenAbilities.description: Sometimes cures the status conditions of the Pokémon's allies.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its flower petals deepen in color through exposure to sunlight. When cloudy weather persists, it does a dance that is thought to be a ritual for summoning the sun.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: The curled hair on its head proves its status as a king. It is said that the longer and curlier the hair, the more respect it earns from its peers.

pokemon.name: Jumpluff

Prevents status conditions in harsh sunlight.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon's moves are unaffected by the target's barriers, substitutes, and the like.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its tail ends with a dexterous, handlike appendage. However, because it uses the tail so much, Aipom's real hands have become rather clumsy.

pokemon.name: Umbreon

pokemon.name: Murkrow

hiddenAbilities.description: Gives priority to the Pokémon's status moves.

pokemon.name: Slowking

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It undertakes research every day to solve the mysteries of the world. However, it apparently forgets everything if the Shellder on its head comes off.

pokemon.name: Misdreavus

hiddenAbilities.description: By floating in the air, the Pokémon receives full immunity to all Ground-type moves.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: A Misdreavus frightens people with a creepy, sobbing cry. It apparently uses its red spheres to absorb the fear of foes as its nutrition.

pokemon.name: Unown

pokemon.pokedexEntry: This Pokémon is shaped like ancient text characters. Although research is ongoing, it is a mystery as to which came first, the ancient writings or the various Unown.

pokemon.name: Wobbuffet

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon anticipates and dodges the attacks of its allies.

pokemon.name: Girafarig

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Light is apparently the source of its energy. It has an extraordinarily vicious disposition and is constantly firing off laser beams.

pokemon.name: Stufful

abilities.description: Halves the damage taken from moves that make direct contact, but doubles that of Fire-type moves.
The Pokémon can't use any held items.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon may infatuate attackers that make direct contact with it.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry and flails about, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.

pokemon.name: Bewear

abilities.description: Halves the damage taken from moves that make direct contact, but doubles that of Fire-type moves.
The Pokémon can't use any held items.

hiddenAbilities.description: Unnerves opposing Pokémon and makes them unable to eat Berries.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It waves its hands wildly in intimidation and warning. Life is over for anyone who doesn't run away as fast as possible.

pokemon.name: Dhelmise

abilities.description: Powers up Steel-type moves.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: The soul of seaweed adrift in the waves became reborn as this Pokémon. It maintains itself with new infusions of seabed detritus and seaweed.

pokemon.name: Mareanie

abilities.description: The Pokémon's attacks become critical hits if the target is poisoned.
The Pokémon's limber body prevents it from being paralyzed.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon has a little of its HP restored when withdrawn from battle.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It plunges the poison spike on its head into its prey. When the prey has weakened, Mareanie deals the finishing blow with its 10 tentacles.

pokemon.name: Toxapex

abilities.description: The Pokémon's attacks become critical hits if the target is poisoned.
The Pokémon's limber body prevents it from being paralyzed.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon has a little of its HP restored when withdrawn from battle.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Those attacked by Toxapex's poison will suffer intense pain for three days and three nights. Post-recovery, there will be some aftereffects.

pokemon.name: Hawlucha

abilities.description: The Pokémon's limber body prevents it from being paralyzed.
Boosts the Speed stat if the Pokémon's held item is used or lost.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon's moves are unimpeded by the Ability of the target.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: With its wings, it controls its position in the air. It likes to attack from above, a maneuver that is difficult to defend against.

pokemon.name: Cacnea

abilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness in a sandstorm.

hiddenAbilities.description: If hit by a Water-type move, the Pokémon has its HP restored instead of taking damage.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Cacnea live in deserts with virtually no rainfall. It battles by swinging its thick, spiked arms. Once a year, a yellow flower blooms.

pokemon.name: Cacturne

abilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness in a sandstorm.

hiddenAbilities.description: If hit by a Water-type move, the Pokémon has its HP restored instead of taking damage.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: After spending thousands of years in harsh deserts, its blood transformed into the same substances as sand. It is nocturnal, so it hunts at night.

pokemon.name: Sandygast

abilities.description: Boosts the Defense stat sharply when the Pokémon is hit by a Water-type move.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness in a sandstorm.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It likes the shovel on its head, so Sandygast will get serious and fight any children who come to take it back.

pokemon.name: Palossand

abilities.description: Boosts the Defense stat sharply when the Pokémon is hit by a Water-type move.

hiddenAbilities.description: Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness in a sandstorm.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Buried beneath the castle are masses of dried-up bones from those whose vitality it has drained.

pokemon.name: Amaura

abilities.description: Normal-type moves become Ice-type moves. The power of those moves is boosted a little.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon makes it snow when it enters a battle.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: This ancient Pokémon was restored from part of its body that had been frozen in ice for over 100 million years.

pokemon.name: Aurorus

abilities.description: Normal-type moves become Ice-type moves. The power of those moves is boosted a little.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon makes it snow when it enters a battle.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Using its diamond-shaped crystals, it can instantly create a wall of ice to block an opponent's attack.

pokemon.name: Rockruff

abilities.description: The Pokémon's keen eyes prevent its accuracy from being lowered.
The Pokémon is full of vitality, and that prevents it from falling asleep.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon's determination boosts its Speed stat every time it flinches.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: This Pokémon has lived with people since times long ago. It can sense when its Trainer is in the dumps and will stick close by its Trainer's side.

pokemon.name: Lycanroc Midday

abilities.description: The Pokémon's keen eyes prevent its accuracy from being lowered.
Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in a sandstorm.

hiddenAbilities.description: The Pokémon's determination boosts its Speed stat every time it flinches.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: Its quick movements confuse its enemies. Well equipped with claws and fangs, it also uses the sharp rocks in its mane as weapons.

pokemon.name: Lycanroc Midnight

abilities.description: The Pokémon's keen eyes prevent its accuracy from being lowered.
The Pokémon is full of vitality, and that prevents it from falling asleep.

pokemon.pokedexEntry: It goads its enemies into attacking, withstands the hits, and in return, delivers a headbutt, crushing their bones with its rocky mane.
